abstract: The Hudson Yards venue will feature programming across disciplines and include other luminaries from music, art, dance and theater.
snippet: The Hudson Yards venue will feature programming across disciplines and include other luminaries from music, art, dance and theater.
lead_paragraph: While the Shed’s unique architectural structure has been revealed, the plans for programming within have been more ambiguous. But on Wednesday, the Shed’s artistic director, Alex Poots, revealed the first batch of commissions for the Hudson Yards venue’s inaugural season.

abstract: In his second attempt to replace Carmen Fariña, the mayor selected Richard A. Carranza, the Houston schools superintendent, who accepted at City Hall.
snippet: In his second attempt to replace Carmen Fariña, the mayor selected Richard A. Carranza, the Houston schools superintendent, who accepted at City Hall.
lead_paragraph: There were two finalists in Mayor Bill de Blasio’s search for a new schools chancellor, and on Monday, just days after being spurned by his first choice, the mayor said the job would go to the runner-up, Richard A. Carranza, the superintendent of the Houston schools.

abstract: Mayor Bill de Blasio pressed for more spending on housing plan last year even as officials saw headwinds after the election of President Trump.
snippet: Mayor Bill de Blasio pressed for more spending on housing plan last year even as officials saw headwinds after the election of President Trump.
lead_paragraph: Under Mayor Bill de Blasio, New York City is financing affordable housing at a breakneck pace, creating or preserving over 24,500 units last year — more than any year on record. To do so, the administration spent $1.1 billion, the most ever by the city in a single year, according to City Hall officials.
